# Narrative_Script

## 1. Applies when
Strong performance, lots of dialogue, protagonist cognition matters, or many linear
story beats.

## 2. This document owns
Concrete performance; dialogue framework; scene beats; the protagonist's subjective
discovery process; cutscene / camera / interaction scripts.

## 3. This document does NOT own
World-truth library; full history; mission-system rules; gameplay parameters.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Scene beats · 3. Dialogue framework · 4. Discovery arcs ·
5. Cutscenes / set-pieces · 6. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Script vs Bible — performance vs objective truth (Script references Bible facts).
- Script vs Level — performance beats vs level triggers.
- Script vs Mission — narrative version vs table/structure version.

## 6. Common audit rules
- No world-truth library maintained here; reference Bible via `REF:`.
- Keep a Script ↔ Mission "narrative vs table" relationship, not duplication.
